# Finding 063
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Duplicate `escapeRegExp` helpers across packages
- File + line(s): `packages/tooling/jskit/src/shared/index.js:326-330`, `packages/tooling/jskit/test/cli.test.js:44-48`, `packages/web/web-runtime-core/src/shared/filesystemComposition.js:22-26`, `packages/surface-routing/src/shared/paths.js:32-36`, `apps/jskit-value-app/src/views/projects/routePaths.js:9-13`
- Why it can drift/fail: The same regex-escaping utility is redefined in multiple packages and tests. Any bug fix or enhancement needs manual propagation.
- Concrete impact: Divergent escaping semantics between routing, tooling, and UI helpers.
- Exact remediation: Provide a shared `escapeRegExp` helper in a core utility package and import it everywhere.

## Resolution
- Justification: This fix would require touching client-side view code (`apps/jskit-value-app/src/views/projects/routePaths.js`), which is currently out of scope per instruction.
- Revisit signal: When client-side changes are unblocked, consolidate `escapeRegExp` into a shared helper and update all call sites including the view route paths.
